【STURDY AND DURABLE】Stainless steel frying pan with lids is made of 304 food grade stainless steel, multi-layer steel composite process, the outer layer is 430 food grade magnetic conductive stainless steel, the middle is high thermal conductivity aluminum alloy material, the inner is food grade 304 stainless steel material, the pan is formed in one piece, using rivet links, safe and solid, healthy and environmentally friendly, physical non-stick, service life of up to 10 years or more.

【NON-STICK FRYING PAN, EASY TO CLEAN】The honeycomb structure of the bottom of the non-stick frying pan can avoid using is sticky pan, making cleaning smoother and saving cleaning time, making your life easier.

【HEALTHY COOKING】Efficient and even heat distribution when using the 10 inch frying pan reduces the cooking temperature of most foods. When cooking eggs, sausages, fish, omelets, you can use less oil and create fresh and delicious food. The frying pan is PFOA-free and can be used without worry.
【DISHWASHER & OVEN SAFE】stainless steel frying pan with lids is dishwasher safe, and hand washing is recommended to extend the life of the skillet. And it is safe to use at 180°C/356°F.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars NOT NON-STICK FOR COOKING; YOU NEED TO OIL PAN
reviews.reviewText: When cooking with this pan it is an ABSOLUTE MUST that you oil or butter the pan in order for your foods (e.g.: eggs) not to stick. The marketing for this pan is a bit deceptive. This is not mentioned in the Amazon advertisement for this pan. However, on the box of the pan it is printed “A little oil/butter required (sic) during cooking”. Therefore, be aware that the non-stick feature is about easy clean-up of the pan and not about cooking without first oiling the pan. When oiled (use oil or butter; don’t use PAM), the frying pan cooks wonderfully. Without oiling the pan scrambled eggs will stick to the bottom of the pan and turn brown.The 2-metal side-grip handles are large, comfortable, and easy to use for safely moving or lifting the pan. The shape and size of the metal grips are very good and very effective. It’s not required that you loop your fingers through the holes to use the metal side grips. You are able to cradle the grips in the palm of your hand, if you desire to lift the pan in that manner. The metal knob on the lid is also large, making it easy and comfortable for removing the lid from the pan. The metal side grips and the metal knob on the lid do become hot, so when moving the frying pan you will need to use heat protection (i.e.: potholders; mitts; towel) for your hands.The frying pan has a solid, balanced feel to it when cooking. And the bottom of the pan “grips” the burner so that the pan doesn’t slide. I appreciate that! Liquids heat readily. When filled 2/3 with cool tap water, it takes about 5-minutes for the water to reach a full boil.Cleaning is a breeze. It is HIGHLY RECOMMENDED that the pans are not washed in a dishwasher. I hand-wash my pots and pans, so that’s no inconvenience for me. But the pan and lid cleans-up so easily that even the dishwasher-user-diehard wouldn’t really be inconvenienced to hand-wash this pan and lid.One “flaw” I noticed is that during washing, water seeps into the knob handle of the lid and gets stuck there. Not good. The “stuck water” cannot seep into the pan or into the food that you are cooking; even so, I don’t like the idea of “stuck water” hanging-out on the underside of the lid’s knob.The frying pan arrives “unassembled”. Using the wrench that is provided, you will need to attach the two metal side grips to the frying pan.On the whole, this is a really nice frying pan, and I am enjoying using it. It’s a good pan and I like it!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful and versatile!
reviews.reviewText: This pan is absolutely beautiful, both inside and outside. Solid, durable, and highly polished stainless steel construction. It arrived well packaged with the handles detached. Handles with hardware and a small tool are included for easy assembly. No instructions, but a cinch to figure out. The instructions for care are printed on the box. Manufacturer suggestion is to use oil or water only and NOT cooking spray. This pan heats QUICKLY. Instructions on the box for stovetop application state "medium to low heat" so, if you have a power burner on your rangetop, too high of a heat source will burn the food surface, without cooking the food throughout. The cleanup is pretty easy. It is not completely non-stick. As indicated in the description by the seller, the design "improves" the non-stick property. It does not state that it is completely non-stick.I fried pork breakfast patties as a test. I did not add oil or water to the pan prior to cooking, thinking that the oil rendered from the patties would be substantial. The patties stuck and blackened a bit. But, to the seller's point, I did not follow the instructions printed on the outside of the box. I did not cook on a low-medium flame, nor did I use oil or water. Once I lowered the flame, I added a touch of water, covered the patties and let them simmer a bit, they came out just fine. The residue left behind was simple enough to clean. I added a bit of very hot water to the pan, let it simmer a bit and the residue slipped right off. I then tried my hand at scrambled eggs, since they always seem to stick on surfaces that claim to be non stick. This time I added a little oil and the eggs fried without sticking to the surface. Once the pan completely cooled, I washed it with a warm soapy water, rinsed and dried it - beautiful! This pan cango from range top, into the oven and to the table for a beautiful presentation, which is an excellent feature.As with most "non-stick" type pans, proper care is important to maintain even heating and the non-stick property, and this pan is no different. Since this pan does not come with enclosed detailed instructions, take heed and be sure to read all instructions on the box. As suggested, I used wooden cooking utensils and did not apply any rough scouring in cleaning. The cleaning is a breeze if you use caution and follow the manufacturer's recommendations. This pan is solid and I anticipate that it will last for many years. For its beauty, solid construction and versatility I would highly recommend this pan.
